    "body_text": [
        {
            "text": "The \u201cKubler- Ross theory of grief\" can be related to the behavior of the masses in the current scenario. According to Ross, there are 5 stages of grief acronym used is DABDA, Denial, Anger, Bargaining, Depression, and Acceptance (Chen et al., 2020). If we observe the behavior of the people initially that could be a mass behavior of denial. When the number of cases increased and fatality occurred we observed that the city of Wuhan were blamed which can be compared to the state of anger in the grief theory. The people used their denial as a tool to overcome the grief of the loss and travelled as if there were no issues. This led the disease to spread even more rapidly, then people isolated the city (Wu and McGoogan, 2020a). Initially enforcing the shutdown was protested massively and bargained to get out of the situation. Then came the depression, the hue and cry for lack of resources followed by acceptance of the current threat. They set up temporary hospitals to build factories to provide consumables like masks and cope with the emergent epidemic (Wu and McGoogan, 2020a). We can still observe similar behaviours\u2019 here people are trying to avoid isolation or going about through their business. It has been observed in Iran that people during pandemics become more prone to common mental disorders like Anxiety and depression (Zandifar and Badrfam, 2020). Indian people are still in the state of denial and are unable to follow through the quarantine process put in place for all the suspected and cases (Banerjee, 2020). People have violated their quarantine and are behaving irresponsibly leading to problematic situations for themselves and their communities. Anxiety levels are rising in India aswell.",
