            "section": "The grief theory",
            "ref_spans": []
        },
        {
            "text": "The behavior of people in the world can be described through the defence mechanisms that Freud had suggested. Freud believed that human beings always desire to be in a pleasurable state. Whenever they face difficulty they try to use their primary defensce mechanisms to get over their difficulties (Kalpan and Sadock, 2000). So in the face of the crisis of corona people of Italy initially repressed their emotions and carried on their work, which then became overwhelmed due to the outbreak of COVID19 leading to the usage of the defence mechanisms of denial and projection. Countries like Italy and India are blaming the Chinese Government and the WHO for the pandemic and hateful messages are prevalent on social media. People are showing anger and hatred towards specific ethnicities hate crimes have increased in the USA and Europe against the Asian people blaming them for the spread of the pandemic (Bults et al., 2011). Hate crimes have increased in India as well. The legal warnings have also failed in many cases where people have collected. To observe such a scenario the protests against the Citizenship Amendment Act are continuing. During the self-imposed curfew in India on 22-03-2020 people came out on streets as if there were celebrations, which was against the law that day which compelled the authorities to take steps in country wide lock down in India.",
            "cite_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 299,
                    "end": 322,
                    "mention": "Kalpan and Sadock, 2000",
                    "ref_id": "BIBREF6"
                },
                {
                    "start": 907,
                    "end": 925,
                    "mention": "Bults et al., 2011",
                    "ref_id": "BIBREF2"
                }
            ],
            "section": "The psychoanalytic theory",
            "ref_spans": []
        },
        {
            "text": "This model given by Rosenstock can also explain the behavior portrayed by the masses. He believed that the perceived health benefit and perceived health risk can tremendously affect the health behavior of people (Bristow, 2010). If the people perceived importance of the health behavior only then they would abide by the advisory if they perceive it otherwise their congruence with the health behavior will not be appropriate. This also has to do with their pre-existing belief system (Morganstein and Ursano, 2020). The misinformation from various sources with negative attitude increase the levels of stress and anxiety (Goyal et al., 2020)",
            "cite_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 213,
                    "end": 226,
                    "mention": "Bristow, 2010",
                    "ref_id": "BIBREF1"
                },
                {
                    "start": 486,
